		Filters
		
			Introduction

This section explains the different filters that are available
				under the Tools menu in Ondex. The first three are stable and the
				most used ones. The rest of them are experimental filters.
			


				When closing a filter, a dialog box pops open and offers users
				three options
			


				- Keep changes: keep changes in the visualisation window but do
				not modify graph (so that you can display concepts which are
				currently invisible in the future)
			


				- Keep and Delete invisible items: keep changes in the
				visualisation window and modify graph accordingly (you know you do
				not wish to work with the rest of the graph from now on)
			


				- Discard all filtering: discard all the filtering steps
				performed on this graph so far
			


				Keep will simply keep the visualisation window as it is (but
				will not alter the actual graph). Keep and apply allows users to not
				only keep the changes made by the filter in the visualisation window
				but also apply the changes to the graph. This means that concepts
				and relations which are currently not visible in the visualisation
				window will be deleted from the graph (rather than hidden). Discard
				will get rid of all the changes made by this or previous filter(s)
				(including the search bar).
			
		
